which indicates,
\begin{eqnarray}
H_{\eta_1\eta_2}^{\sigma_1\sigma_2}(k_x,k_y,k_z)= H_{{\eta}_1 {\eta}_2}^{\bar{\sigma}_1\bar{\sigma}_2}(-k_x,k_y,k_z).
\label{eq:mx_spin}
\end{eqnarray}
With Eq.(\ref{eq:mx_spin}), one gets $H_{AB}^{\uparrow\uparrow}(0,k_y,k_z)= H_{AB}^{\downarrow\downarrow}(0,k_y,k_z)$ and $H_{AB}^{\uparrow\downarrow}(0,k_y,k_z)= H_{AB}^{\downarrow\uparrow}(0,k_y,k_z)$, which proves
\begin{eqnarray}
\mathbf{Im}\left[f(0,k_y,k_z)\right]=0, ~\mathbf{Re}\left[g(0,k_y,k_z)\right]=0.
\label{eq:f_reg}
\end{eqnarray}
